<TEXT>
a minister his wife and two of his 
daughters were found shot to death inside their rural home sunday 
morning after he failed to show up for services police said 
the bodies were discovered around 8 am inside the parsonage 
next door to the olive branch united brethren church by a church 
trustee who came looking for the rev robert pelley said st 
josephs county sgt charles feirrell 
pelley his wife dawn and daughters jonel 8 and joelene 6 
had been shot at close range feirrell said he did not have the 
ages of the minister and his wife 
there were no signs of forced entry and investigators had a 
suspect and a motive in the case but no arrest had been made by 
late sunday feirrell said the suspect resided locally he said 
the pelleys have two older daughters and a teenage son but 
they were out of town over the weekend he said 
pelley was pastor for the past 2 years at the church in this 
rural residential area on the outskirts of lakeville nearly seven 
miles south of south bend 
