<TEXT>
three or four b2 stealth bombers could 
have handled the 1986 libyan bombing raid better than the nearly 
100 planes that carried out the raid a highranking air force 
official said saturday 
were talking about an airplane that just gives us much more 
flexibility than anything right now in the strategic deterrent 
family said gen bernard s randolph commander of the air force 
systems command 
if the b2 had been in the air force arsenal three years ago 
three or four flying from the united states and refueling en route 
could have bombed libya with complete surprise more efficiency and 
accuracy than the europeanbased planes that did the job he said 
randolph addressed the annual news conference of the 
aviationspace writers association 
the bomber can carry up to 80 500pound conventional bombs or 20 
nuclear weapons can fly from low levels to altitudes of about 
50000 feet and personifies a technological leap into the next 
century he said 
the subsonic twoman aircraft will weigh more than 350000 
pounds with weapons and fuel and have a range of more than 6000 
nautical miles or more than 10000 with one refueling randolph 
said 
the range is greater than that of a b52 the mainstay of the 
nations bomber fleet for three decades he said the plane will be 
able to fly from any airfield that can handle a boeing 727 he said 
with two domestic and two overseas bases the united states will 
be able to attack any land mass in the world randolph said 
the b2 is scheduled to make its first flight this summer 
last week defense secretary richard cheney said the 
administration would delay purchasing the plane pending a review of 
the program which has been estimated to cost 70 billion for 132 
planes 
</TEXT>
