<TEXT>
a drug war situation room unveiled by president 
bush last week and one like it in california may be the nations 
most sophisticated antismuggling weapons yet but some question 
whether such hightech wizardry can do much 
bush dedicated the customs servicecoast guard interdiction 
center thursday during a visit to miami where he also addressed 
top latin american drugfighting officials at an international 
conference 
think of this as one of americas drug war situation rooms as 
our early warning network against narcotics bush said after 
watching a computer simulation of a drug interdiction in which 
smugglers were tracked through the skies and seas off miami and 
intercepted by jets and speedboats 
the command control communications and intelligence center or 
c3i is in a squat peachcolored building southwest of miami in a 
field dotted with radar antennas 
information from a network of land sea and air radar monitored 
by the federal aviation administration customs the coast guard 
and the pentagon will be displayed on a video system 
specialists will compare radar data with faa flight plans field 
updates and intelligence reports to keep track of up to 5000 boats 
and planes across more than 12 million square miles in the eastern 
united states 
c3i west in riverside calif has directed air interdiction 
west of houston since august 
my sources within the defense department say they dont have 
anything to match c3i from a technical standpoint its a very 
sophisticated system designed specifically for drug interdiction 
said rep glenn english dokla former chairman of the house 
subcommittee responsible for overseeing the drug war 
theres no better way we could spend this 33 million said 
customs commissioner william von raab standing in front of a 
customs blackhawk helicopter outside the center thursday 
we were absolutely defenseless in our air borders five years 
ago you could fly anywhere into the united states and not stand a 
snowballs chance of getting caught von raab said now we are 
well out in front of the smugglers and we are never going to fall 
behind again 
others arent so confident they point to longstanding problems 
such as interagency rivalry a lack of equipment such as radar 
planes and boats and a shortage of intelligence 
you have to recognize youre going up against an entity that 
is bringing in 150 billion a year roughly half of our total 
defense spending with 67 billion a year from the us 
government english said 
cocaine seizures virtually nonexistent before the 1980s are 
growing nationwide 
the coast guard hauled in 14591 pounds in fiscal 1988 up from 
12950 in 1987 customs seized 138808 pounds in fiscal 1988 
compared to a combined 140419 in 1986 and 1987 
marijuana seizures by both agencies have dropped sharply in what 
officials say is a sign that the law is forcing smugglers to move 
to lower risk higher profit cocaine 
but authorities intercept at best only about 10 percent of the 
3500 flights and 4500 boat trips smugglers make each year 
according to the congressional office of technology assessment 
upwards of 18 million pounds of marijuana 300000 pounds of 
cocaine and 13000 pounds of heroin will be smuggled into the 
country this year the office estimates 
before the c3i center can improve these numbers gaps in the 
