hospitalized since march 16 said the islamic republic news agency 
monitored in nicosia 
tabari was born in 1917 in sari a city in the northern 
mazandaran province and joined the communist tudeh party when it 
was formed in 1941 
he fled to the soviet union when the party was declared illegal 
in 1947 and worked as an announcer for radio moscow fluent in 
seven languages he also wrote and translated poetry and did 
research into linguistics irna said 
